This paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as cognate projection, inflection generation, and phoneme-to-grapheme conversion, which are typically categorized under the arXiv CS sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of language models and precise alignment of training data suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the mention of state-of-the-art results suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE) and statistical learning (cs.SD) approaches.
